title: About
text:
What I do for fun

I love whenever I can get some time with my guitar, maybe with some paper and a pencil to strech my creative side. I also love trying things I’ve never tried before, or getting outside and exploring places I have never seen or been to.


Anyone is free to reach out if they ever want to go hiking or rock climbing!

title: Joshua Paul Cohen
text: Hi there! I’m Joshua. I’m currently a Environmental Data Science student at the UCSN Bren School. But I also like bugs, music, hiking, rock climbing, and all the cool stuff.

title: Joshua Paul Cohen
text:
Education
Master of Environmental Data Science (Expected June 2025) Bren School of Environmental Science & Management – University of California, Santa Barbara (UCSB)
Bachelor of Science in Environmental Science (May 2020)  Minors in Chesapeake Regional Studies, Music  Washington College (WAC), Chestertown, MD 

I’m currently looking to be hired!
I have significant GIS experience, did my undergrad along the Cheaspeake Bay, and am motivated to use my skills to preserve the environment.

Send me questions and inquiries at the below links if interested!
